    {
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 12, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 47},
      "id": 17,
      "options": {
        "code": {"language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false},
        "content": "# Alert response runbooks\n\nStart with the alert name, severity, affected resource, and start time. Confirm recovery in the Recently Resolved table.\n\n- **Watchdog or alert lifecycle:** check Prometheus and Alertmanager `up`, the watchdog rule, and this Grafana dashboard.\n- **Service availability:** check the named target, Docker health through the operator workflow, and recent Loki logs.\n- **Cribl delivery:** check Alloy, queue use, TLS, the exact endpoint, and the Cribl listener. An enqueue failure means data loss.\n- **Local telemetry:** check Loki or Prometheus health, disk space, and the matching Alloy writer.\n- **Host capacity:** check the matching CPU, load, memory, swap, filesystem, inode, disk, or file-descriptor panel before changing capacity.\n- **Service latency or errors:** check the named Traefik service, request rate, downstream health, and recent logs.\n- **Certificate expiry:** replace the certificate through the approved Ansible process and confirm Traefik loaded it.\n\nFull operator source: `docs/observability-operations.md#alert-response-runbooks` in this release checkout.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Alert Response Runbooks",
      "type": "text"
    }
  ],
